Kirillov-Reshetikhin conjecture : the general case
The motivation for this work is the study of the properties of positive weighted Chow motives over local and global fields. In this paper, we present an approach to the Kirillov-Reshetikhin conjecture on positive motive classification in terms of deformations of algebraic varieties. We show that the Kirillov-Reshetikhin conjecture is a special case of a more general conjecture on the structure of positive motive deformations. We give a criterion for the consistency of this conjecture in the case of local fields.

Let $k$ be a local field. Let $M$ be a positive motive. We write $M$ uniquely as a finite conjunction of simple motives. Let $M_0$ be the smallest positive motive; that is, the intersection of all simple motives. We say that $M$ is a deformation of $M_0$ if there exists a $k$-linear homomorphism $\varphi: M_0 \to M$ such that the following properties hold.

(i) $\varphi$ is an injective map on simple motives;
(ii) $\varphi$ induces an isomorphism on the quotient $M_0/M$;
(iii) if $\varphi(M_0) = M_0$, then $\varphi$ is an isomorphism.

